question.text: Select the correct route for the passage of sperms in male frogs.

options.text: Testes  <math><mo>→</mo></math>   Bidder's canal  <math><mo>→</mo></math>   Kidney  <math><mo>→</mo></math>   Vasa efferentia  <math><mo>→</mo></math>  Urinogenital duct  <math><mo>→</mo></math>  Cloaca

Testes  <math><mo>→</mo></math>  Vasa efferentia  <math><mo>→</mo></math>  Kidney  <math><mo>→</mo></math>  Seminal Vesicle  <math><mo>→</mo></math>  Urinogenital duct  <math><mo>→</mo></math>  Cloaca
Testes  <math><mo>→</mo></math>  Vasa efferentia  <math><mo>→</mo></math>  Bidder's canal  <math><mo>→</mo></math>  Ureter  <math><mo>→</mo></math>  Cloaca
Testes <math><mo>→</mo></math> Vasa efferentia <math><mo>→</mo></math> Kidney <math><mo>→</mo></math> Bidder's canal <math><mo>→</mo></math> Urinogenital duct <math><mo>→</mo></math> Cloaca

solution.text: In the male frog, the sperms will move from Testes → Vasa efferentia → Kidney → Bidder's canal → Urinogenital duct → Cloaca.
